  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `1.6.1`\r\nOS & Version: Windows 7 x64\r\nSystem: Core i5 2400, 16GB, SSD\r\nNet speed: 512kbps\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nusing geth --fast cache 8192\r\ngeth should roll back exactly 2048 blocks during sync failed and dropping peer\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\ngeth roll back 10's of thousand blocks.\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\nSometimes happens.\r\n\r\n#### Backtrace\r\n\r\n>INFO [06-12|07:41:04] Imported new block headers               count=2048 elapsed=356.020ms number=2216689 hash=22c2a0…9ae625 ignored=0\r\nINFO [06-12|07:41:18] Imported new state entries               count=71   elapsed=33.001ms  processed=6253537 pending=39572\r\nINFO [06-12|07:41:28] Imported new state entries               count=62   elapsed=27.001ms  processed=6253599 pending=40564\r\nINFO [06-12|07:41:29] Imported new block receipts              count=175  elapsed=43.002ms  number=2180710 hash=834dd6…ec836d ignored=0\r\nINFO [06-12|07:41:30] Imported new block receipts              count=355  elapsed=77.004ms  number=2181065 hash=f7aeae…e6eb99 ignored=0\r\n>WARN [06-12|07:41:54] Rolled back headers                      count=2048 header=2216689->2214641 fast=2181065->2181065 block=6->6\r\nWARN [06-12|07:41:54] Synchronisation failed, dropping peer    peer=17adb5cee5271064 err=\"retrieved hash chain is invalid\"\r\n>INFO [06-12|07:42:03] Imported new block headers               count=0    elapsed=3.000ms   number=2181257 hash=fffc4e…ee259a ignored=192",
